Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.96,0:00:34.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得它很可爱  对不对\N{\rEnglish}You think this is cute, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.80,0:00:38.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得你们有真正的情感共鸣\N{\rEnglish}You think there's a real connection there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.12,0:00:40.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你喂它吃东西\N{\rEnglish}So you feed it,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.80,0:00:42.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给它穿衣服\N{\rEnglish}you dress it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.05,0:00:46.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs24}九 条 命
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.92,0:00:48.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是猫并不在乎你的死活\N{\rEnglish}But a cat doesn't care if you live or die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.64,0:00:51.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只要有人每天给它吃两顿饭就行\N{\rEnglish}as long as someone gives it Friskies twice a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.76,0:01:04.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是人们极度渴求陪伴\N{\rEnglish}But people are so desperate for someone to hold onto
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.04,0:01:06.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已经饥不择食\N{\rEnglish}they'll take whatever they can get.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.64,0:01:10.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是在出事后几个月  在街头捡到他的\N{\rEnglish}I found him on the street, months after the accident
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.48,0:01:12.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我总把他打扮成正雄的样子\N{\rEnglish}and I dress him like Masao.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.60,0:01:16.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我知道是我儿子附身在猫上回来找我了\N{\rEnglish}I know my son has come back to me in this cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.32,0:01:19.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是不管你有多孤单\N{\rEnglish}But no matter how lonely you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.88,0:01:23.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,猫总归不是人\N{\rEnglish}a cat is not a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.40,0:01:47.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢  你真会安慰人\N{\rEnglish}Okay. Super helpful, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.63,0:01:49.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fnSTKaiti\fs18}布兰德航空
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.96,0:01:51.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,市场部希望能把新广告牌投入使用\N{\rEnglish}Oh, so marketing wants sign-off on the new billboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.05,0:01:53.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fnSTKaiti\fs18}梦想成真
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.88,0:01:53.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得如何\N{\rEnglish}What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.48,0:01:55.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能修图修得有点狠了\N{\rEnglish}It might be a little heavy on the Photoshop.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.44,0:01:56.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来架真正的F16\N{\rEnglish}Get me a real F-16.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.56,0:01:57.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拍点真实的照片\N{\rEnglish}We'll take some real pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.72,0:01:59.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不  他们说没有这个预算\N{\rEnglish}No, they said they don't have the budget for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.52,0:02:00.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就把市场部开了\N{\rEnglish}Fire the marketing department!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.96,0:02:03.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你要把整个市场部都开掉吗\N{\rEnglish}You wanna fire the entire marketing department?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.32,0:02:06.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是  我要真正的F16战隼战斗机  下一件事\N{\rEnglish}No. I wanna fly a real F-16. What's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.36,0:02:08.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你让我提醒你\N{\rEnglish}I'm supposed to remind you,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.08,0:02:09.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,劳拉留了两条留言\N{\rEnglish}Lara's left two messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.44,0:02:10.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她为什么打电话\N{\rEnglish}Why is she calling?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.96,0:02:12.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为她是你妻子\N{\rEnglish}Because she's your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.56,0:02:14.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,之后的媒体见面会\N{\rEnglish}I put together some talking points
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.00,0:02:16.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我帮你整理了要点\N{\rEnglish}for your press conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.40,0:02:17.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你多大来着\N{\rEnglish}How old are you again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.76,0:02:18.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,28岁\N{\rEnglish}Twenty-eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.88,0:02:19.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我已经跟媒体打交道28年了\N{\rEnglish}That's how long I've been talking to the press.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.00,0:02:21.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,放心吧\N{\rEnglish}I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.08,0:02:22.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,先生  我们准备好了\N{\rEnglish}Sir, we're ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.08,0:02:25.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不如你今天跟我一起跳吧\N{\rEnglish}Why don't you jump with me today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.76,0:02:28.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,算了吧  我刚吃完早餐\N{\rEnglish}Oh, yeah, no. I just had breakfast, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.32,0:02:29.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来吧\N{\rEnglish}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.84,0:02:31.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爸  不行\N{\rEnglish}Dad, I can't. I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.36,0:02:33.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\rEnglish}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.32,0:02:37.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,胆小鬼\N{\rEnglish}Chicken!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.64,0:02:43.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,说得真狠  爸\N{\rEnglish}Good one, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.28,0:03:02.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,漂亮\N{\rEnglish}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.36,0:03:03.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常厉害\N{\rEnglish}Very nice, very nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:06.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,着陆很完美\N{\rEnglish}Perfect landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.52,0:03:07.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\rEnglish}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.92,0:03:10.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢大家  谢谢\N{\rEnglish}Thank you very much. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.88,0:03:12.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大家上午好\N{\rEnglish}Good morning, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.20,0:03:13.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里景色太好了\N{\rEnglish}What an incredible view.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.44,0:03:16.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是说一大早见到各位真是赏心悦目\N{\rEnglish}And I mean all of you that I get to look at this fine morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.40,0:03:17.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢各位抽空前来\N{\rEnglish}Thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.80,0:03:19.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等一个月后\N{\rEnglish}Now, when we open this building
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.48,0:03:20.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这座大楼竣工\N{\rEnglish}one month from today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.08,0:03:23.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,布兰德大楼会是北美最高的建筑\N{\rEnglish}The FireBrand Tower will be the tallest building in North America.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.12,0:03:26.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也就是说这么多年来被迫在那破地方工作\N{\rEnglish}And that means that we can finally move out of that dump
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.44,0:03:28.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们终于可以搬出去了\N{\rEnglish}we've all been forced to work in all these years down the block.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.68,0:03:29.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,跟我们讲讲芝加哥吧\N{\rEnglish}Tell us about Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.92,0:03:32.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,布兰德先生  您对百丽宫大厦有什么看法\N{\rEnglish}Mr. Brand, any comment on the Paragon Tower?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.52,0:03:35.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你是说他们在芝加哥堆砌起来的简易房吗\N{\rEnglish}Oh, you mean that tin shack they're gluing together over there in Chicago?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.84,0:03:36.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我就不说什么了\N{\rEnglish}No. No comment on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.96,0:03:39.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,据说会比您的大楼高18米左右\N{\rEnglish}Rumor is they're beating you by 60 feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.40,0:03:41.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不会的  不可能\N{\rEnglish}Well, no. There's not a chance of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.28,0:03:43.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不会  我非常愿意继续回答问题\N{\rEnglish}No, no. Look, I'd love to answer more questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.20,0:03:44.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但我得回办公室去了\N{\rEnglish}but I gotta get back to the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.60,0:03:49.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的  我希望这个项目做快点\N{\rEnglish}All right. I wanna move fast here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.36,0:03:51.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让法务部连夜把这个看一遍\N{\rEnglish}Have legal review this overnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.16,0:03:52.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们一直在忙大楼的事\N{\rEnglish}They're all tied up with the tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.00,0:03:54.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我知道我们得让他开心\N{\rEnglish}Listen, I know we got to keep him happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.64,0:03:56.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是不能让这座大楼耽误我们...\N{\rEnglish}but we can't let this building distract us from...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.64,0:03:58.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,怎么  你有别的安排吗\N{\rEnglish}Why? You've got something better to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.68,0:04:00.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,媒体见面会顺利吗\N{\rEnglish}How was the press conference?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.00,0:04:02.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很显然浪费了我的时间\N{\rEnglish}Well, apparently it was a distraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.96,0:04:05.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我安排了一些人去考察公开募股的事了\N{\rEnglish}I pulled some staff to explore a public offering.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.64,0:04:08.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等等  我让你把我的公司卖掉了吗\N{\rEnglish}I'm sorry. Did I ask you to sell my company?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.16,0:04:09.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,请问是要投标吗\N{\rEnglish}Are we taking bids?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.32,0:04:10.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,加利能卖多少钱\N{\rEnglish}How much can we get for Gary?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.84,0:04:12.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们粗略估计了一下...\N{\rEnglish}We ran some rough numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.96,0:04:15.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好  首先  为什么媒体在问我芝加哥的事\N{\rEnglish}Yeah. Well, first, why is the press asking me about Chicago?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.20,0:04:16.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你占了上风  你的更大\N{\rEnglish}You're winning. Yours is bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.04,0:04:19.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新宣传标语终于出来了\N{\rEnglish}Well, finally there's our new slogan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.60,0:04:21.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,竣工典礼准备得如何了\N{\rEnglish}Where are we with the opening ceremony?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.20,0:04:23.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们会在整座大楼上装满烟花\N{\rEnglish}We're gonna rig the entire building with fireworks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.32,0:04:25.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以  我一剪彩\N{\rEnglish}Oh, so, wait. When I cut the ribbon...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.28,0:04:26.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,烟花就会绽放\N{\rEnglish}Fireworks go off.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.36,0:04:28.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天哪  伊恩  这主意太棒了\N{\rEnglish}Oh, my God. Ian, that is just spectacular,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.56,0:04:31.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们又不是在庆祝国庆\N{\rEnglish}you know, if we were doing a Fourth of July celebration
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.12,0:04:32.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也不是在庆祝啤酒节\N{\rEnglish}or a really rousing Oktoberfest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.64,0:04:33.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,汤姆  不能...\N{\rEnglish}Tom, we can't keep...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.80,0:04:37.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们马上就要建成北半球最高的建筑物了\N{\rEnglish}Look, we are just about to cap off the tallest building in the Northern Hemisphere
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.36,0:04:39.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要是竣工典礼不够宏大我还怎么吹牛逼\N{\rEnglish}and I can't brag about it if I don't own it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.84,0:04:40.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是\N{\rEnglish}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.92,0:04:43.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真是浪费时间\N{\rEnglish}This is the distraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.56,0:04:48.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好了  假装刚才什么都没发生\N{\rEnglish}Okay, everybody, let's pretend that that didn't just happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.96,0:05:05.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-这是什么  -是惊喜\N{\rEnglish}- What's that? - It's a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.28,0:05:06.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的生日礼物吗\N{\rEnglish}For my birthday?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.56,0:05:09.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-你在看什么  -在看爸爸\N{\rEnglish}- What are you watching? - Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.96,0:05:11.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他让你录的吗\N{\rEnglish}Did he tell you to record this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.80,0:05:13.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有  我只是想看他\N{\rEnglish}No, but I just wanted to see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.40,0:05:14.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你看\N{\rEnglish}Look. Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.72,0:05:16.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这么多年来被迫在这破地方工作\N{\rEnglish}And that means that we can finally move out of that dump
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.00,0:05:19.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,终于可以搬出去了\N{\rEnglish}we've all been forced to work in all these years down the block.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.60,0:05:22.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你看了多少遍了\N{\rEnglish}How many times have you watched this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.44,0:05:24.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,83遍\N{\rEnglish}Eighty-three.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.88,0:05:26.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在84遍了\N{\rEnglish}And now it's 84.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.52,0:05:27.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们很担心成本\N{\rEnglish}We're worried about costs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.04,0:05:30.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以才来开董事会啊\N{\rEnglish}Well, that's why we call this a "Board meeting."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.54,0:05:33.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fnSTKaiti\fs18}您妻子来电
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.36,0:05:33.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让她留言吧\N{\rEnglish}Please take a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.72,0:05:35.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-汤姆  有很多问题需要考虑  -我知道\N{\rEnglish}- Tom, these are serious concerns. - I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.80,0:05:37.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-我明白...  -劳拉·布兰德\N{\rEnglish}- Look, I understand... - Lara Brand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.80,0:05:39.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fnSTKaiti\fs18}劳拉·布兰德来电
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.28,0:05:41.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-劳拉·布兰德  -没事  出去接\N{\rEnglish}- Lara Brand. - Oh, no, go ahead. Just take it outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.12,0:05:47.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伊恩  汤姆在哪里  我联系不上他\N{\rEnglish}Ian, where's Tom? I can't get ahold of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.32,0:05:48.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他在开董事会  走不开\N{\rEnglish}I can't pry him away from the Board.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.04,0:05:52.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,各位听我说  我考虑过你们担心的问题\N{\rEnglish}I wanna show you all that I take your concerns very seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.04,0:05:55.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的运营成本比上个季度高了30%\N{\rEnglish}Our operating costs are up 30% from last quarter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.76,0:05:57.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我最大的担心是\N{\rEnglish}And my first concern is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.22,0:05:59.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伊恩为什么开始搞公开募股的事了\N{\rEnglish}why is Ian coming at us with this IPO crap?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.08,0:06:01.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他一整天都在开会吗\N{\rEnglish}He's been with the Board all day?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.40,0:06:02.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他很难挤出时间\N{\rEnglish}It's hard to get Tom's attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.68,0:06:03.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许我应该加入董事会\N{\rEnglish}Maybe I should join the Board.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.96,0:06:06.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者你可以来坐我的位子  真的\N{\rEnglish}Or you can take my job. Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.44,0:06:08.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伊恩跟我们提过想法\N{\rEnglish}Ian approached us with the idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.28,0:06:10.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他准备了一份非常诱人的方案\N{\rEnglish}He's put together a very attractive proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.64,0:06:13.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,公开募股就意味着我们会有一笔大收入\N{\rEnglish}A public offering means a big payday for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.28,0:06:16.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们已经把好几年的利润投进了那座楼  汤姆\N{\rEnglish}Now, we've sunk years of revenue into that building, Tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.20,0:06:17.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,差不多该回本了\N{\rEnglish}It's time to cash out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.64,0:06:19.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们有很多现金  不是吗\N{\rEnglish}Come on, we got plenty of cash, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.00,0:06:21.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是为什么\N{\rEnglish}And why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.08,0:06:23.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们做航空  做连锁超市  做手机\N{\rEnglish}Because we built airlines and retail chains and phone companies,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.04,0:06:26.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是没人会记得\N{\rEnglish}but no one is gonna remember any of those
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.32,0:06:27.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为转手太多次\N{\rEnglish}because they keep changing hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.72,0:06:29.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是一百年后\N{\rEnglish}But 100 years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.48,0:06:31.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大家透过窗子看到那座大楼\N{\rEnglish}when people look out their windows and they see that tower,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.04,0:06:33.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够看到"布兰德"这个名字\N{\rEnglish}they're gonna see the name "Brand"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.96,0:06:35.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这将是他们永远不会忘记的名字\N{\rEnglish}and that's a name they will never forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.84,0:06:39.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而我绝对不愿意卖掉这份财富\N{\rEnglish}And that is not something that I am willing to sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.20,0:06:41.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,企业不是用来帮你作秀的  汤姆\N{\rEnglish}We're not running a charity for your ego, Tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.48,0:06:43.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  那就来玩个游戏\N{\rEnglish}Okay. Well, then instead, let's play a little game.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.72,0:06:45.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就当好玩了\N{\rEnglish}You know, just for the fun of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.52,0:06:49.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果公司抬头里有你的名字请举手\N{\rEnglish}Raise your hand if your name is on the company letterhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.36,0:06:51.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-汤姆  -不  来吧  我们只是投个票\N{\rEnglish}- Tom... - No, no. Come on, we'll just call it a vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.32,0:06:54.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-汤姆  -51%\N{\rEnglish}- Tom... - Fifty-one percent!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.24,0:06:55.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,赢了的感觉真好\N{\rEnglish}Feels good to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.00,0:06:57.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你们可以在我葬礼上卖了我的股份\N{\rEnglish}You can sell shares at my funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.76,0:07:00.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,下次伊恩想当执行总裁的时候\N{\rEnglish}And the next time Ian wants to play CEO,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.16,0:07:03.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以一起炒了他\N{\rEnglish}we can fire him together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.88,0:07:05.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-能借一步说话吗  -现在不行\N{\rEnglish}- Hey, can I borrow you for a minute? - Not now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.92,0:07:07.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,关于那座塔\N{\rEnglish}It's about the tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.76,0:07:13.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我已经跟你爸说了我们的塔高出100英尺\N{\rEnglish}I already talked to your dad about this. We're 100 feet taller.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.16,0:07:15.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我知道那是项目规划\N{\rEnglish}I know that's the projection.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.20,0:07:16.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但那只是参考\N{\rEnglish}But that's printed to scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.36,0:07:17.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,芝加哥的比我们的高了60英尺\N{\rEnglish}Chicago's beating us by 60.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.76,0:07:19.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我漏了什么东西吗  我们的更高才对\N{\rEnglish}Am I missing something here? We're taller.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.82,0:07:20.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们天花板里有很多钢筋\N{\rEnglish}There's too much steel in their roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.84,0:07:21.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以呢\N{\rEnglish}So?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.00,0:07:24.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以额定承重760吨\N{\rEnglish}So that's rated for 760 tons,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.07,0:07:24.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在上面什么都没有\N{\rEnglish}and there's nothing on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.88,0:07:26.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但如果他们这样放钢材\N{\rEnglish}But if they laid that much steel...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.68,0:07:28.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们还没有完成\N{\rEnglish}They're not done.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.84,0:07:29.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不  这不在他们的计划内\N{\rEnglish}No, that's not in their plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.96,0:07:30.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们知道我们有他们的计划\N{\rEnglish}They know we have their plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.04,0:07:32.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们想让我们觉得我们赢了\N{\rEnglish}They want us to think we're winning
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.38,0:07:33.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但他们已经批准了那个计划\N{\rEnglish}but they got a permit for that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.48,0:07:34.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在他们要比我们高60英尺了\N{\rEnglish}and they are beating us by 60 feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.00,0:07:36.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大卫\N{\rEnglish}David!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.48,0:07:38.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  先保密\N{\rEnglish}Right. Keep this quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.96,0:07:42.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伊恩  在马德里那午睡时间之前\N{\rEnglish}Oh, Ian, let's make that call to Madrid
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.65,0:07:43.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给那边的人打个电话\N{\rEnglish}before they take their siesta.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.76,0:07:44.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然\N{\rEnglish}Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.64,0:07:47.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知道  我们是有清洁工的\N{\rEnglish}You know, we do have janitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.64,0:07:49.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-我一直在忙  -我有东西要给你\N{\rEnglish}- Yeah. I've been busy. - I got you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.35,0:07:57.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fnSTKaiti\fs18}为你成为男子汉而准备的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.64,0:07:59.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢了  爸\N{\rEnglish}Thanks, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.94,0:08:01.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fnSTKaiti\fs18}火兰德公司
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.53,0:08:03.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\fnSTKaiti\fs18}为你成为男子汉而准备的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.32,0:08:08.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很抱歉打扰你吃晚餐  但我需要那份报告\N{\rEnglish}I'm sorry to break up your dinner, but I need that report.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.00,0:08:11.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,告诉你老婆我来买单\N{\rEnglish}Well, tell your wife the check's on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.08,0:08:13.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但她明年还是会有周年纪念的\N{\rEnglish}Yeah, but she gets another anniversary next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.84,0:08:15.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我并不关心\N{\rEnglish}I don't really care.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.16,0:08:19.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,打扰一下  你看到我妻子了吗\N{\rEnglish}Oh, excuse me, have you seen my wife anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.32,0:08:20.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她长什么样\N{\rEnglish}What does she look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.60,0:08:24.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她是全世界最美的女人\N{\rEnglish}She is the most beautiful woman in the entire world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.92,0:08:27.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许我见过她  让我看一看\N{\rEnglish}Oh, well, maybe I have seen her. Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.44,0:08:30.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,找到了  是她吗\N{\rEnglish}Oh, here we go. Is this her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.44,0:08:32.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给她打个电话吧\N{\rEnglish}Oh, let's give her a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.92,0:08:35.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,今天很忙  我错过什么了吗\N{\rEnglish}Yeah, it was a busy day. What did I miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.48,0:08:37.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我生日是上个月\N{\rEnglish}Uh, my birthday was last month.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.12,0:08:39.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在跟我开玩笑吗\N{\rEnglish}You're joking me right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.80,0:08:41.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你还不如让我去工作\N{\rEnglish}You're gonna have to give me more to work with than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.96,0:08:46.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-糟糕  不会是今天吧  -明天\N{\rEnglish}- Oh, damn it. It's not today? - Tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.12,0:08:47.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就好  我还没错过\N{\rEnglish}Oh, well, then I haven't missed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.60,0:08:49.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,年度父亲\N{\rEnglish}Father of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.12,0:08:50.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们买什么送她\N{\rEnglish}So, what did we get her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.56,0:08:51.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们什么都没买\N{\rEnglish}Oh, we didn't get her anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.80,0:08:54.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你忙到连说五分钟话的时间都没有\N{\rEnglish}You were too busy to talk for five minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.24,0:08:55.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我买了一个化妆包\N{\rEnglish}so I got her a makeup kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.88,0:08:58.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不能说那个化妆包是我们俩送的吗\N{\rEnglish}Oh, well, couldn't we say that the makeup kit's from both of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.00,0:09:00.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-不能  -好吧\N{\rEnglish}- No. - Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.08,0:09:02.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我该给她买点什么\N{\rEnglish}What should I get her?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.76,0:09:05.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许你应该问问她想要什么\N{\rEnglish}Maybe you should ask her what she wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.08,0:09:06.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,趁她还没上大学\N{\rEnglish}Try getting to know her a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.64,0:09:08.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,试着了解她一下吧\N{\rEnglish}before she heads off to college.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.24,0:09:10.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,别这样  还有七年呢\N{\rEnglish}Come on. I still got seven years left.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.32,0:09:12.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者是六年  我开玩笑呢\N{\rEnglish}Or, no, six years. I'm kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.52,0:09:13.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就是这样带大卫的吗\N{\rEnglish}Is this how you raised David?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.92,0:09:15.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我儿子现在还不错\N{\rEnglish}My son turned out just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.60,0:09:17.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他为了见你不得不去你那工作\N{\rEnglish}He had to apply for a job to see his dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.72,0:09:19.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然  他母亲有完全监护权\N{\rEnglish}Well, of course. His mother got full custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.24,0:09:20.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我那个律师太糟糕\N{\rEnglish}I had a terrible lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.32,0:09:21.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你参加丽贝卡的派对的时候\N{\rEnglish}When you come to Rebecca's party...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.80,0:09:24.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有一个月  我们就要建成最高的建筑\N{\rEnglish}Look, we are a month away from opening the tallest building in...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.28,0:09:26.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,汤姆  你去参加丽贝卡聚会的时候\N{\rEnglish}Tom! When you come to Rebecca's party,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.00,0:09:29.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你得到场并且带一份精美的礼物\N{\rEnglish}you gotta be here and you have to bring an exceptional gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.08,0:09:31.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爸爸\N{\rEnglish}Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.32,0:09:33.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宝贝儿\N{\rEnglish}Hey, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.64,0:09:36.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天啊  睡衣真漂亮\N{\rEnglish}Oh, my Goodness. Those are such fancy pajamas.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.36,0:09:37.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,确实很漂亮\N{\rEnglish}Yeah, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.48,0:09:38.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-这不是睡衣  -不是吗\N{\rEnglish}- They're not pajamas. - They're not?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.00,0:09:40.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但你是不是该睡觉了  她什么时候睡觉\N{\rEnglish}But isn't it your bedtime? What time is her bedtime?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.20,0:09:42.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她和我们一起去\N{\rEnglish}She's coming with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.68,0:09:43.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,妈妈说我可以去见梅厄\N{\rEnglish}Mom says I get to meet the Mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.04,0:09:45.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真的吗\N{\rEnglish}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.52,0:09:47.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真是父女情深的一刻\N{\rEnglish}Quality father-daughter bonding time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.16,0:09:49.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里会有吃的吗\N{\rEnglish}Will there be food?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.84,0:09:50.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一万刀一份\N{\rEnglish}It's $10,000 a plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.00,0:09:52.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你得像皇后一样优雅的吃饭\N{\rEnglish}You're gonna eat like a queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.08,0:09:53.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会有披萨吗\N{\rEnglish}Will there be pizza?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.56,0:09:55.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有  一万刀的披萨\N{\rEnglish}Yes, $10,000 pizza.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.40,0:10:02.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,儿童基金在市长的领导下蒸蒸日上\N{\rEnglish}The children's fund has thrived under the Mayor's leadership.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.56,0:10:05.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了保证爱德华兹市长能从中获利\N{\rEnglish}And to make sure Mayor Edwards gets something out of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.32,0:10:07.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他将把投票年龄下调至十岁\N{\rEnglish}he's gonna lower the voting age to ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.48,0:10:10.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每个人都会问我为什么我的丈夫\N{\rEnglish}Everyone asks me why my husband
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.92,0:10:13.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会来组织慈善活动\N{\rEnglish}is hosting a charity event.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.12,0:10:15.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为汤姆很爱孩子\N{\rEnglish}The truth is Tom loves children.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.64,0:10:17.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他说他们造出了最好的智能手机\N{\rEnglish}He says they make the best smartphones.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.12,0:10:19.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我没听懂\N{\rEnglish}I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.40,0:10:20.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她刚才呛了你爸\N{\rEnglish}She just burned your dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.00,0:10:22.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们说和孩子相处的时光\N{\rEnglish}They say there is no substitute
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.84,0:10:24.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是无可替代的\N{\rEnglish}for time with your children.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.56,0:10:27.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道  在这个房间里  钱更重要\N{\rEnglish}Although, we know, in this room, money comes close.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.48,0:10:31.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这也就是为什么这个慈善基金会这么受欢迎\N{\rEnglish}And that's why this charity is so popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.04,0:10:33.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你没有时间陪孩子\N{\rEnglish}If you don't have time for kids,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.52,0:10:35.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以把你的钱拿走来减轻你的负罪感\N{\rEnglish}we'll ease your guilt by taking your dough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.32,0:10:39.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这也就是为什么汤姆·布兰德同意\N{\rEnglish}Which is why Tom Brand has agreed to host this benefit
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.04,0:10:42.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再组织七年慈善活动\N{\rEnglish}for the next seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.20,0:10:47.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,废话不多说  有请我的丈夫\N{\rEnglish}So without further ado, please welcome my husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.08,0:10:49.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个没种的家伙  汤姆·布兰德\N{\rEnglish}a real pussy cat, Tom Brand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.52,0:10:55.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以  今天是个大日子\N{\rEnglish}So, today is the big day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.56,0:10:56.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你想好要什么了吗\N{\rEnglish}Have you thought about what you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.04,0:10:58.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想要一只猫\N{\rEnglish}I want a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.24,0:10:59.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们那栋楼不能带宠物\N{\rEnglish}Oh, I don't think our building takes pets.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.56,0:11:00.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可那栋楼是你的呀\N{\rEnglish}You own the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.80,0:11:02.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等等  你去年是不是也说要一只猫\N{\rEnglish}Wait, didn't you ask for a cat last year?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.28,0:11:04.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对  你给我买了一个足球桌\N{\rEnglish}Yeah, and you got me a foosball table.
